President Biden met with Prime Minister Draghi of Italy on the sidelines of the G7 Summit. They discussed deepening bilateral ties and celebrated the 160th anniversary of diplomatic relations between the United States and Italy. They pledged to cooperate closely in overcoming the pandemic, including through the G7 commitment to donate COVID-19 vaccines globally. They also expressed gratitude for Italy's support for Afghan peace and security. President Biden praised Italy's leadership of the G20 and its focus on people, planet, and prosperity. The two leaders agreed to collaborate on global challenges and shared foreign policy priorities, such as China, Russia, and Libya.